  19 def test_parse_no_timezone_different_default():
  20     tz = iso8601.FixedOffset(2, 0, "test offset")
  21     d = iso8601.parse_date("2007-01-01T08:00:00", default_timezone=tz)
  22     assert d == datetime.datetime(2007, 1, 1, 8, 0, 0, 0, tz)
  23     assert d.tzinfo == tz
  24 
  25 def test_parse_utc_different_default():
  26     """Z should mean 'UTC', not 'default'.
  27 
  28     """
  29     tz = iso8601.FixedOffset(2, 0, "test offset")
  30     d = iso8601.parse_date("2007-01-01T08:00:00Z", default_timezone=tz)
  31     assert d == datetime.datetime(2007, 1, 1, 8, 0, 0, 0, iso8601.UTC)

  33 @pytest.mark.parametrize("invalid_date, error_string", [
  34     ("2013-10-", "Unable to parse date string"),
  35     ("2013-", "Unable to parse date string"),
  36     ("", "Unable to parse date string"),
  37     (None, "Expecting a string"),
  38     ("wibble", "Unable to parse date string"),
  39     ("23", "Unable to parse date string"),
  40     ("131015T142533Z", "Unable to parse date string"),
  41     ("131015", "Unable to parse date string"),
  42     ("20141", "Unable to parse date string"),
  43     ("201402", "Unable to parse date string"),
  44     ("2007-06-23X06:40:34.00Z", "Unable to parse date string"),  # https://code.google.com/p/pyiso8601/issues/detail?id=14
  45     ("2007-06-23 06:40:34.00Zrubbish", "Unable to parse date string"),  # https://code.google.com/p/pyiso8601/issues/detail?id=14
  46     ("20114-01-03T01:45:49", "Unable to parse date string"),
  47 ])
  48 def test_parse_invalid_date(invalid_date, error_string):
  49     assert isinstance(invalid_date, str) or invalid_date is None  # Why? 'cos I've screwed up the parametrize before :)
  50     with pytest.raises(iso8601.ParseError) as exc:
  51         iso8601.parse_date(invalid_date)
  52     assert exc.errisinstance(iso8601.ParseError)
  53     assert str(exc.value).startswith(error_string)

  76     ("2006-10-20T15:34:56.123+0230", datetime.datetime(2006, 10, 20, 15, 34, 56, 123000, iso8601.FixedOffset(2, 30, "+02:30")), "2006-10-20T15:34:56.123000+02:30"),  # https://code.google.com/p/pyiso8601/issues/detail?id=18

  86 def test_parse_valid_date(valid_date, expected_datetime, isoformat):
  87     parsed = iso8601.parse_date(valid_date)
  88     assert parsed.year == expected_datetime.year
  89     assert parsed.month == expected_datetime.month
  90     assert parsed.day == expected_datetime.day
  91     assert parsed.hour == expected_datetime.hour
  92     assert parsed.minute == expected_datetime.minute
  93     assert parsed.second == expected_datetime.second
  94     assert parsed.microsecond == expected_datetime.microsecond
  95     assert parsed.tzinfo == expected_datetime.tzinfo
  96     assert parsed == expected_datetime
  97     assert parsed.isoformat() == expected_datetime.isoformat()
  98     copy.deepcopy(parsed)  # ensure it's deep copy-able
  99     pickle.dumps(parsed)  # ensure it pickles
 100     if isoformat:
 101         assert parsed.isoformat() == isoformat
 102     assert iso8601.parse_date(parsed.isoformat()) == parsed  # Test round trip
